Sutherland Says Ireland Should Build on Positive Reaction

-- B y   J o e   B r e n n a n
-- 
2011-09-22T12:52:03Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-22/sutherland-says-ireland-should-build-on-positive-reaction.html
 Peter Sutherland, non-executive
chairman of Goldman Sachs International, said it would be
“foolhardy” for the Irish government not to build on positive
reaction to the government’s banking and fiscal measures.  Sutherland, a former European Commissioner, said at an
event in Dublin today the government should frontload addtional
budget cuts to reduce its deficit.  To contact the reporter on this story:
